message.content:
Analysis of Main Target Image:

• Block Count and Layers:  
  – There are 5 total blocks in the structure.  
     1 yellow rectangular block on the bottom  
     2 orange cylinders standing vertically as “columns”  
     1 yellow rectangular block resting on top of the columns  
     1 orange triangular prism piece forming the “roof”  
  – Functionally, the structure can be viewed in three main layers:  
     Layer 1: Bottom yellow rectangle  
     Layer 2: The two vertical orange cylinders  
     Layer 3: Top yellow rectangle with the orange triangular block set above it  

• Spatial Relationships:  
  – The bottom yellow rectangular block lies flat on the ground.  
  – The two orange cylinders stand vertically, placed side by side on the bottom rectangle.  
  – A second yellow rectangular block sits on top of these two cylinders, spanning across them.  
  – Centered on that upper rectangle, an orange triangular prism is placed as a roof.

Selection of Required Blocks from Dictionary:

• Needed Indices and Rationale:  
  – Yellow Rectangles (used twice: bottom and top): Block #1  
    (It is a yellow rectangular prism oriented horizontally, matching both top and bottom bars.)  
  – Orange Cylinders (used twice, both upright): Block #6  
    (This is the vertically oriented orange cylinder.)  
  – Orange Triangular Prism (roof): Block #14  
    (This triangular wedge has the same front‐to‐back slope as shown in the target roof.)  

Hence, the final required list of dictionary blocks is:  
• Block 1 (twice)  
• Block 6 (twice)  
• Block 14 (once)

Assembly Order:

{
   Step1: Move block with index 1    // place the bottom yellow rectangle
   Step2: Move block with index 6    // first vertical orange cylinder
   Step3: Move block with index 6    // second vertical orange cylinder
   Step4: Move block with index 1    // top yellow rectangle
   Step5: Move block with index 14   // orange triangular roof piece
}
